The Advisory Council shall consist of the following members, selected by each organization from which the member is a representative:
A representative from the Department;
A representative from the Maryland Parent-Teacher Association;
A representative from the Maryland State Teachers Association;
A representative from the Public School Superintendents Association of Maryland;
Representatives from each local school system;
A representative from the Maryland Association of Boards of Education;
A representative from the Maryland Association of Counties;
A representative from the Governor's Council on Physical Fitness and Sport;
A representative of the Professional Organization for Health, Physical Education, Recreation, and Dance;
A representative from an institution of higher education having a health and physical education teacher education program;
A representative from Special Olympics of Maryland;
A representative from the Department of Health and Mental Hygiene;
A representative from the American Academy of Pediatrics; and
Representatives from the following health organizations:
The American Heart Association;
The American Cancer Society; and
The American Diabetes Association.

The Advisory Council shall:
Develop and coordinate programs in collaboration with public schools to educate students regarding the importance of:
Physical activity and physical movement;
The relationship of physical activity to a healthy lifestyle and improved fitness;
The relationship between healthy eating, physical activity, and maintaining a healthy weight; and
The value of physical activity and its relationship to improved academic achievement and stress reduction;
Identify promising health and physical education practices in the State;
Build a network of health and physical education professionals to share information and strengthen partnerships;
Support successful health and physical education programs in the State and encourage the expansion of those programs; and
Consult with organizations represented on the Advisory Council as appropriate.
